itemDescription: track and field athlete from Great Britain (1890-1960)

wikipedia_page.main: William Craig Moore (5 April 1890 – 12 May 1956) was a British track and field athlete who competed in the 1912 Summer Olympics. In 1912 he was eliminated in the first round of the 1500 metres competition. He also helped Great Britain to qualify for the final in the 3000 metre team race. In the final, however, he was the weakest link of the team. Nevertheless, he was awarded with a bronze medal.
